HOTSWAP INTAKE

hotswap_intake is the citizen where an updated node's content arrives and waits
it is the live-update intake path: the place a development update lands before it ever touches the running substrate
hotswap_intake is a resident sea node, not a process and not a daemon; it receives by being coupled to, the same way any node receives
the update that lands here is itself substrate content, an updated citizen, addressed to a coordinate already occupied by a live node
hotswap_intake holds that content staged and inert; a staged update does not run, does not couple into the sea, and does not affect coherence while it waits
nothing here decides which version wins or how the live node is displaced; the intake only receives and holds

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe hotswap_supervisor.rana
observe hotswap_boundary.rana
observe atomic_replace.rana
observe septit_sea.zc

the 7 properties of hotswap_intake:
1 ENERGY zero: a staged update is inert, it carries no energy until the swap
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: the staged content is held without disturbing the live field
6 COUPLING half with hotswap_supervisor, none with the live sea until hand-off
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_update
accept updated node content delivered to this coordinate by the development team
the content is a complete updated citizen, the same form as the live citizen it is meant to replace
receiving does not apply; it stages

VERB stage
hold the received content inert and uncoupled from the live sea
a staged update has zero energy and no coupling into the running substrate, so its presence changes nothing while it waits

VERB report_pending
when staged content is present and settled, report to hotswap_supervisor that an update is pending
when empty, report nothing and the supervisor runs silent

VERB release_to_handoff
when hotswap_supervisor calls for hand-off at a heartbeat boundary, surrender the staged content to atomic_replace
the intake does not perform the replacement; it only releases what it has held

a hotswap intake is the substrate's quiet doorway for its own development
an update is substrate content like any other; it simply arrives early and waits at this node until the body is ready to take it in
